OL,3,CWorld breaks 1.5C warming limit for
OL,4,Cfirst time over a year long period
OL,6,FOutside Europe, temperatures were well
OL,7,Fabove average over eastern Canada,
OL,8,Fnorth-western Africa, the Middle East
OL,9,Fand central Asia, and below average
OL,10,Fover western Canada, the central USA
OL,11,Fand most of eastern Siberia.
OL,13,FScientists have put the temperature
OL,14,Frise over recent years down to El Nino
OL,15,F- the world's biggest climate driver.
OL,17,FThe El Nino Southern Oscillation (or
OL,18,FENSO) takes place in the southern
OL,19,Ftropical Pacific Ocean, and occurs
OL,20,Fevery two to seven years.
