OL,3,CWorld breaks 1.5C warming limit for
OL,4,Cfirst time over a year long period
OL,6,FEl Nino is the name given to the warm
OL,7,Fphase of this natural cycle compared
OL,8,Fto its counterpart La Nina - the cool
OL,9,Fphase.
OL,11,FDuring El Nino events, the ocean heat
OL,12,Fis released into the atmosphere and
OL,13,Fredistributed around the globe. It is
OL,14,Fno coincidence the hottest years on
OL,15,Frecord occur during El Nino years.
OL,17,FEl Nino began to weaken in the
OL,18,Fequatorial Pacific, but marine air
OL,19,Ftemperatures in general remained at an
OL,20,Funusually high level, Copernicus said.
